cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.AR 

This paper discusses the architecture of Network Functions Virtualization (NFV) for Virtualized Wireless Sensor and Actuator Networks (VWSANs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the need for dynamic, elastic, and scalable provisioning of gateways, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also presents a prototype built using the OpenStack platform, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the integration of new sensors and actuators, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the need for accommodating new application domains, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
